Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sona DAP, also known as Fauji Fertilizer FFC DAP, is a type of fertilizer with 50kg bags containing 18% nitrogen and 46% phosphorus, commonly referred to as di-ammonium phosphate (DAP). In the context of agriculture, DAP is a water-soluble ammonium phosphate derived from the reaction of ammonia and phosphoric acid. It is a highly concentrated phosphatic fertilizer, with 46% P2O5 and 18% nitrogen (N). It is recommended for all crops as a foundational fertilizer to be applied during sowing. This application promotes robust root development and energizes plant processes. DAP boasts excellent solubility, exceeding 90%, making it one of the most soluble phosphatic fertilizers available. This high solubility enables it to be applied through fertigation after planting. Additionally, due to its nitrogen content, DAP tends to have an acidic effect once the nitrification process is complete. In industrial applications, DAP finds utility as a fire retardant in commercial firefighting products. It also serves other purposes, such as a metal finisher, yeast nutrient, and a sugar purifier. Urea is a concentrated straight nitrogenous fertilizer that contains 46% nitrogen, which is a major plant nutrient. Nitrogen is a vital component of chlorophyll which is necessary for the photosynthesis process. It is applied to promote vegetative growth of crops and orchards in splits (basal & top-dressing). In irrigated crops, Mostly, Urea is applied on the standing crop followed by irrigation to minimize its losses. In rain fed areas, it is often spread just before rain to minimize losses through volatilization process. ‚ÄúSona Urea‚Äù produced by FFC is in prilled form and at FFBL in Granular form. Granular Urea has the advantage of ease of application on standing crops because of large size granules. Its efficiency is relatively better in high water demanding crops like rice.

Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Urea is high moisture absorbent therefore it should be stored in sealed and well enclosed bags .¬† Crops: Garlic ,Wheat, Rice, Maize,Cotton, Sugarcane, Potato, Citrus, Mango, Mango(Desahri), Mango(Sindhri), Mango-Chaunsa, Mango-Dussehri, Mango-Langra, Mung Bean, Chilli, Garlic, Onion, Okra, Ginger, Tomato, Spring Onion, Cucumber, Mung bean, Mash, Masoor, Chickpea, Brinjal , Sesame, Sunflower, Tobacco, Mustard, Guava, Musk Melon, Water Melon, Orange -Pineapple, Orange -Mosambi, Orange -Salustiana, Orange -Shakri, Orange, Orange -Marsh Early

Urea is a concentrated straight nitrogenous fertilizer that contains 46% nitrogen, which is a major plant nutrient. Nitrogen is a vital component of chlorophyll which is necessary for the photosynthesis process. It is applied to promote vegetative growth of crops and orchards in splits (basal & top-dressing). In irrigated crops, Mostly, Urea is applied on the standing crop followed by irrigation to minimize its losses. In rain fed areas, it is often spread just before rain to minimize losses through volatilization process. ‚ÄúSona Urea‚Äù produced by FFC is in prilled form and at FFBL in Granular form. Granular Urea has the advantage of ease of application on standing crops because of large size granules. Its efficiency is relatively better in high water demanding crops like rice.

Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Urea is high moisture absorbent therefore it should be stored in sealed and well enclosed bags .¬† Crops: Garlic ,Wheat, Rice, Maize,Cotton, Sugarcane, Potato, Citrus, Mango, Mango(Desahri), Mango(Sindhri), Mango-Chaunsa, Mango-Dussehri, Mango-Langra, Mung Bean, Chilli, Garlic, Onion, Okra, Ginger, Tomato, Spring Onion, Cucumber, Mung bean, Mash, Masoor, Chickpea, Brinjal , Sesame, Sunflower, Tobacco, Mustard, Guava, Musk Melon, Water Melon, Orange -Pineapple, Orange -Mosambi, Orange -Salustiana, Orange -Shakri, Orange, Orange -Marsh Early

Ranger is highly useful as an insect resistance management (IRM) tool. Ranger is suitable for IPM (integrated pest management) programs, that are used to manage pest damage by the most economical means, and with the least possible hazard to people, property, and the environment.

Sulfur is an essential 4th major nutrient, classified as a secondary macronutrient, it is used in the formation of amino acids, protein, oils, and chlorophyll, and activates certain enzymes/vitamins. Plants take up sulfur as Sulphate ion (SO4), G. sulfur (elemental sulfur) when added to the soil, its oxidation starts in the presence of oxygen, moisture & bacteria, and it releases H+ ions, which acidify the soil, minimizing currently applied nitrogen fertilizer losses and make available already present fixed nutrients in the soil, sulfur also conditions & reclaim salt-affected soils, thus increase soil fertility & yield.  Role: 1. Helps in lowering the pH of the soil and thus increases the efficiency of other fertilizers. 2. Enhances the process of photosynthesis and improves the quality of crops for end users. 3. Helps to reclaim salt-affected soils. 4. Acts as antifungal.  Method of Application: Use this product with irrigation or spread it by hand on soil or place it along the plant rows.  Registration Details: Product is registered in Pakistan. SKU: Green Sulfur is available in 1 Kg and 20 Kg bags.

Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Urea is high moisture absorbent therefore it should be stored in sealed and well enclosed bags .¬† Crops: Garlic ,Wheat, Rice, Maize,Cotton, Sugarcane, Potato, Citrus, Mango, Mango(Desahri), Mango(Sindhri), Mango-Chaunsa, Mango-Dussehri, Mango-Langra, Mung Bean, Chilli, Garlic, Onion, Okra, Ginger, Tomato, Spring Onion, Cucumber, Mung bean, Mash, Masoor, Chickpea, Brinjal , Sesame, Sunflower, Tobacco, Mustard, Guava, Musk Melon, Water Melon, Orange -Pineapple, Orange -Mosambi, Orange -Salustiana, Orange -Shakri, Orange, Orange -Marsh Early

Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Urea is high moisture absorbent therefore it should be stored in sealed and well enclosed bags .¬† Crops: Garlic ,Wheat, Rice, Maize,Cotton, Sugarcane, Potato, Citrus, Mango, Mango(Desahri), Mango(Sindhri), Mango-Chaunsa, Mango-Dussehri, Mango-Langra, Mung Bean, Chilli, Garlic, Onion, Okra, Ginger, Tomato, Spring Onion, Cucumber, Mung bean, Mash, Masoor, Chickpea, Brinjal , Sesame, Sunflower, Tobacco, Mustard, Guava, Musk Melon, Water Melon, Orange -Pineapple, Orange -Mosambi, Orange -Salustiana, Orange -Shakri, Orange, Orange -Marsh Early

Glyphosate is a widely used herbicide and the active ingredient in many weed-killing products. It is a broad-spectrum herbicide, meaning it is effective against a wide range of plants. Sulfur is an essential 4th major nutrient, classified as a secondary macronutrient, it is used in the formation of amino acids, protein, oils, and chlorophyll, and activates certain enzymes/vitamins. Plants take up sulfur as Sulphate ion (SO4), G. sulfur (elemental sulfur) when added to the soil, its oxidation starts in the presence of oxygen, moisture & bacteria, and it releases H+ ions, which acidify the soil, minimizing currently applied nitrogen fertilizer losses and make available already present fixed nutrients in the soil, sulfur also conditions & reclaim salt-affected soils, thus increase soil fertility & yield.  Role: 1. Helps in lowering the pH of the soil and thus increases the efficiency of other fertilizers. 2. Enhances the process of photosynthesis and improves the quality of crops for end users. 3. Helps to reclaim salt-affected soils. 4. Acts as antifungal.  Method of Application: Use this product with irrigation or spread it by hand on soil or place it along the plant rows.  Registration Details: Product is registered in Pakistan. SKU: Green Sulfur is available in 1 Kg and 20 Kg bags.

Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Urea is high moisture absorbent therefore it should be stored in sealed and well enclosed bags .¬† Crops: Garlic ,Wheat, Rice, Maize,Cotton, Sugarcane, Potato, Citrus, Mango, Mango(Desahri), Mango(Sindhri), Mango-Chaunsa, Mango-Dussehri, Mango-Langra, Mung Bean, Chilli, Garlic, Onion, Okra, Ginger, Tomato, Spring Onion, Cucumber, Mung bean, Mash, Masoor, Chickpea, Brinjal , Sesame, Sunflower, Tobacco, Mustard, Guava, Musk Melon, Water Melon, Orange -Pineapple, Orange -Mosambi, Orange -Salustiana, Orange -Shakri, Orange, Orange -Marsh Early

Ranger is a broad-spectrum insecticide that belongs to the phenylpyrazole chemical family and is widely used on Rice, Maize, and Sugarcane crops. Ranger disrupts the insect central nervous system by blocking GABA-gated chloride channels and glutamate-gated chloride (glucl) channels. this causes hyperexcitation of contaminated insects‚Äô nerves and muscles. Ranger is highly useful as an insect resistance management (IRM) tool. Ranger is suitable for IPM (integrated pest management) programs, that are used to manage pest damage by the most economical means, and with the least possible hazard to people, property, and the environment.

Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Urea is high moisture absorbent therefore it should be stored in sealed and well enclosed bags .¬† Crops: Garlic ,Wheat, Rice, Maize,Cotton, Sugarcane, Potato, Citrus, Mango, Mango(Desahri), Mango(Sindhri), Mango-Chaunsa, Mango-Dussehri, Mango-Langra, Mung Bean, Chilli, Garlic, Onion, Okra, Ginger, Tomato, Spring Onion, Cucumber, Mung bean, Mash, Masoor, Chickpea, Brinjal , Sesame, Sunflower, Tobacco, Mustard, Guava, Musk Melon, Water Melon, Orange -Pineapple, Orange -Mosambi, Orange -Salustiana, Orange -Shakri, Orange, Orange -Marsh Early

Sulfur is an essential 4th major nutrient, classified as a secondary macronutrient, it is used in the formation of amino acids, protein, oils, and chlorophyll, and activates certain enzymes/vitamins. Plants take up sulfur as Sulphate ion (SO4), G. sulfur (elemental sulfur) when added to the soil, its oxidation starts in the presence of oxygen, moisture & bacteria, and it releases H+ ions, which acidify the soil, minimizing currently applied nitrogen fertilizer losses and make available already present fixed nutrients in the soil, sulfur also conditions & reclaim salt-affected soils, thus increase soil fertility & yield.  Role: 1. Helps in lowering the pH of the soil and thus increases the efficiency of other fertilizers. 2. Enhances the process of photosynthesis and improves the quality of crops for end users. 3. Helps to reclaim salt-affected soils. 4. Acts as antifungal.  Method of Application: Use this product with irrigation or spread it by hand on soil or place it along the plant rows. Sona DAP, also known as Fauji Fertilizer FFC DAP, is a type of fertilizer with 50kg bags containing 18% nitrogen and 46% phosphorus, commonly referred to as di-ammonium phosphate (DAP). In the context of agriculture, DAP is a water-soluble ammonium phosphate derived from the reaction of ammonia and phosphoric acid. It is a highly concentrated phosphatic fertilizer, with 46% P2O5 and 18% nitrogen (N). It is recommended for all crops as a foundational fertilizer to be applied during sowing. This application promotes robust root development and energizes plant processes. DAP boasts excellent solubility, exceeding 90%, making it one of the most soluble phosphatic fertilizers available. This high solubility enables it to be applied through fertigation after planting. Additionally, due to its nitrogen content, DAP tends to have an acidic effect once the nitrification process is complete. In industrial applications, DAP finds utility as a fire retardant in commercial firefighting products. It also serves other purposes, such as a metal finisher, yeast nutrient, and a sugar purifier. Sarsabz Nitrophos (NP) is a granulated fertilizer in which each grain has equal amounts of Phosphorus (P) 20% & Nitrogen (N) 22%. It contains dual Nitrogen (Nitrate: readily available to the plants and Ammonical: available after its conversion to nitrate through the process of nitrification). Consistent and longer use of Sarsabz NP also improves soil health. Sona DAP, also known as Fauji Fertilizer FFC DAP, is a type of fertilizer with 50kg bags containing 18% nitrogen and 46% phosphorus, commonly referred to as di-ammonium phosphate (DAP). In the context of agriculture, DAP is a water-soluble ammonium phosphate derived from the reaction of ammonia and phosphoric acid. It is a highly concentrated phosphatic fertilizer, with 46% P2O5 and 18% nitrogen (N). It is recommended for all crops as a foundational fertilizer to be applied during sowing. This application promotes robust root development and energizes plant processes. DAP boasts excellent solubility, exceeding 90%, making it one of the most soluble phosphatic fertilizers available. This high solubility enables it to be applied through fertigation after planting. Additionally, due to its nitrogen content, DAP tends to have an acidic effect once the nitrification process is complete. In industrial applications, DAP finds utility as a fire retardant in commercial firefighting products. It also serves other purposes, such as a metal finisher, yeast nutrient, and a sugar purifier. Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Nitrophos (NP) is a granulated fertilizer in which each grain has equal amounts of Phosphorus (P) 20% & Nitrogen (N) 22%. In addition to this, NP being a highly acidic product with a pH of 3.5, is the most suitable fertilizer for soils that have a high pH and are alkaline in nature.¬† The balanced combination of Nitrogen & Phosphorus is ideal for plant growth and development. It contains dual Nitrogen (Nitrate: readily available to the plants and Ammonical: available after its conversion to nitrate through the process of nitrification). Consistent and longer use of Sarsabz NP also improves soil health. Sarsabz Nitrophos (NP) can be applied universally on all types of soils, but is more effective where the soils have high pH and are alkaline in nature. In many crops it could be effectively applied at planting and at early growth stages of the crops. Each grain has equal amounts of N & P, hence the nutrients are equally distributed throughout the field.

Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Urea is high moisture absorbent therefore it should be stored in sealed and well enclosed bags .¬† Crops: Garlic ,Wheat, Rice, Maize,Cotton, Sugarcane, Potato, Citrus, Mango, Mango(Desahri), Mango(Sindhri), Mango-Chaunsa, Mango-Dussehri, Mango-Langra, Mung Bean, Chilli, Garlic, Onion, Okra, Ginger, Tomato, Spring Onion, Cucumber, Mung bean, Mash, Masoor, Chickpea, Brinjal , Sesame, Sunflower, Tobacco, Mustard, Guava, Musk Melon, Water Melon, Orange -Pineapple, Orange -Mosambi, Orange -Salustiana, Orange -Shakri, Orange, Orange -Marsh Early

Sulfur is an essential 4th major nutrient, classified as a secondary macronutrient, it is used in the formation of amino acids, protein, oils, and chlorophyll, and activates certain enzymes/vitamins. Plants take up sulfur as Sulphate ion (SO4), G. sulfur (elemental sulfur) when added to the soil, its oxidation starts in the presence of oxygen, moisture & bacteria, and it releases H+ ions, which acidify the soil, minimizing currently applied nitrogen fertilizer losses and make available already present fixed nutrients in the soil, sulfur also conditions & reclaim salt-affected soils, thus increase soil fertility & yield.  Role: 1. Helps in lowering the pH of the soil and thus increases the efficiency of other fertilizers. 2. Enhances the process of photosynthesis and improves the quality of crops for end users. 3. Helps to reclaim salt-affected soils. 4. Acts as antifungal.  Method of Application: Use this product with irrigation or spread it by hand on soil or place it along the plant rows.  Registration Details: Product is registered in Pakistan. SKU: Green Sulfur is available in 1 Kg and 20 Kg bags.

Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Urea is high moisture absorbent therefore it should be stored in sealed and well enclosed bags .¬† Crops: Garlic ,Wheat, Rice, Maize,Cotton, Sugarcane, Potato, Citrus, Mango, Mango(Desahri), Mango(Sindhri), Mango-Chaunsa, Mango-Dussehri, Mango-Langra, Mung Bean, Chilli, Garlic, Onion, Okra, Ginger, Tomato, Spring Onion, Cucumber, Mung bean, Mash, Masoor, Chickpea, Brinjal , Sesame, Sunflower, Tobacco, Mustard, Guava, Musk Melon, Water Melon, Orange -Pineapple, Orange -Mosambi, Orange -Salustiana, Orange -Shakri, Orange, Orange -Marsh Early

Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Urea is high moisture absorbent therefore it should be stored in sealed and well enclosed bags .¬† Crops: Garlic ,Wheat, Rice, Maize,Cotton, Sugarcane, Potato, Citrus, Mango, Mango(Desahri), Mango(Sindhri), Mango-Chaunsa, Mango-Dussehri, Mango-Langra, Mung Bean, Chilli, Garlic, Onion, Okra, Ginger, Tomato, Spring Onion, Cucumber, Mung bean, Mash, Masoor, Chickpea, Brinjal , Sesame, Sunflower, Tobacco, Mustard, Guava, Musk Melon, Water Melon, Orange -Pineapple, Orange -Mosambi, Orange -Salustiana, Orange -Shakri, Orange, Orange -Marsh Early

Role: 1. Helps in lowering the pH of the soil and thus increases the efficiency of other fertilizers. 2. Enhances the process of photosynthesis and improves the quality of crops for end users. 3. Helps to reclaim salt-affected soils. 4. Acts as antifungal.  Method of Application: Use this product with irrigation or spread it by hand on soil or place it along the plant rows.  Registration Details: Product is registered in Pakistan. SKU: Green Sulfur is available in 1 Kg and 20 Kg bags.

Sarsabz Urea releases nitrogen into soil which is thereafter taken up in by the plants. Once applied to the soil onion crops, Sarsabz Urea undergoes vital transformations and breaks up into ammonium form and this total process is dependent on soil moisture. As soon as Sarsabz Urea dissolves in the soil, it forms around it a zoning layer of high pH and ammonia concentration turning the soil to be acidic and toxic at the same level. Sarsabz Urea is available as prills that are crystalline white and highly resistant to moisture and thus facilitate long time storage.¬† Sarsabz Urea has the highest nitrogen content, equal to 46 percent. This percentage is much higher than other nitrogenous fertilizers available in the market. The nutrient composition rendered by urea enhances the productivity of the soil and enriches its nutrient constituency. Providing each plant with relevant element needed, urea sustains plant life. Sarsabz Urea can be applied in various forms, it can be spread in bulk alone or can also be mixed with other fertilizers before application. When urea is applied on acidic soils of lower pH i.e below 7.0, it should be incorporated into the soil as soon as possible. Sarsabz Urea is high moisture absorbent therefore it should be stored in sealed and well enclosed bags .¬† Crops: Garlic ,Wheat, Rice, Maize,Cotton, Sugarcane, Potato, Citrus, Mango, Mango(Desahri), Mango(Sindhri), Mango-Chaunsa, Mango-Dussehri, Mango-Langra, Mung Bean, Chilli, Garlic, Onion, Okra, Ginger, Tomato, Spring Onion, Cucumber, Mung bean, Mash, Masoor, Chickpea, Brinjal , Sesame, Sunflower, Tobacco, Mustard, Guava, Musk Melon, Water Melon, Orange -Pineapple, Orange -Mosambi, Orange -Salustiana, Orange -Shakri, Orange, Orange -Marsh Early

Ranger is a broad-spectrum insecticide that belongs to the phenylpyrazole chemical family and is widely used on Rice, Maize, and Sugarcane crops. Ranger disrupts the insect central nervous system by blocking GABA-gated chloride channels and glutamate-gated chloride (glucl) channels. this causes hyperexcitation of contaminated insects‚Äô nerves and muscles. Ranger is highly useful as an insect resistance management (IRM) tool. Ranger is suitable for IPM (integrated pest management) programs, that are used to manage pest damage by the most economical means, and with the least possible hazard to people, property, and the environment.

V Transform is crystalline Zinc 21%. Zinc activate enzymes that are responsible for the synthesis of certain proteins. It is used in the formation of chlorophyll and carbohydrates. Zinc application with Nitrogen application is usually recommended.

Sentinel is a highly effective broad-spectrum systemic foliar fungicide for the control of a wide range of leaf and stems diseases in cereals. Composed with the active ingredient Propiconazole and formulation of an emulsifiable concentrate is absorbed by the assimilating parts of the plant, the majority within one hour. It is transported upwards and acts on the fungal pathogen inside the plant at the stage of the first haustoria formation. It stops the development of fungi by interfering with the biosynthesis of sterols in cell membranes. The best results are achieved when the disease is in the early stage of development.
